00:48:26,500 --> 00:48:28,070
Welcome in.

566
00:48:29,210 --> 00:48:30,860
Hello.

567
00:48:49,800 --> 00:48:53,580
Has it been 10 years now since your parents opened this convenience store?

568
00:48:53,580 --> 00:48:55,130
Yes.

569
00:48:56,840 --> 00:49:01,940
Then, when your father left our construction company,

570
00:49:01,940 --> 00:49:04,170
I thought you'd ask Jung Kyung

571
00:49:04,170 --> 00:49:06,880
to help your father out.

572
00:49:06,880 --> 00:49:09,860
My father's business is his own to take care of.

573
00:49:12,910 --> 00:49:16,360
You must be one to not ask for favors often.

574
00:49:16,360 --> 00:49:19,040
Wise people know to make requests of others,

575
00:49:19,040 --> 00:49:21,640
to the right person in the right place.

576
00:49:22,810 --> 00:49:26,320
I, too, must have become wiser with age.

577
00:49:26,320 --> 00:49:29,320
I'm thinking of asking for a favor.

578
00:49:32,370 --> 00:49:35,690
There's an opening for a position of professor

579
00:49:35,690 --> 00:49:38,500
at the department of string music at Seoryeong University.

580
00:49:38,500 --> 00:49:40,690
Why don't you try applying?

581
00:49:42,530 --> 00:49:48,270
It's an opening created because a violin professor retired, but there's no reason another violinist has to fill that position.

582
00:49:49,990 --> 00:49:51,930
But that position, Jung Kyung-

583
00:49:51,930 --> 00:49:54,710
Ah, Jung Kyung does want

584
00:49:54,720 --> 00:49:56,730
to be a professor at Seoryeong University.

585
00:49:56,730 --> 00:50:00,220
She's being stubborn, saying she'll do as she pleases.

586
00:50:03,810 --> 00:50:08,600
But people each have a particular place that suits them.

587
00:50:08,600 --> 00:50:11,810
Her place is the director of our foundation.

588
00:50:11,810 --> 00:50:14,090
Not a professor.

589
00:50:17,300 --> 00:50:19,910
I still don't think...

590
00:50:25,990 --> 00:50:29,720
Maybe you believe you're not good enough to be a professor at Seoryeong University?

591
00:50:30,570 --> 00:50:33,280
Yes, well, that's true.

592
00:50:35,380 --> 00:50:38,250
Level doesn't have anything to do with skill.

593
00:50:44,210 --> 00:50:47,560
It's about who trusts you and supports you.

594
00:50:47,560 --> 00:50:50,100
That could be even more important.

595
00:50:50,100 --> 00:50:52,630
And after all, it could be considered luck

596
00:50:52,630 --> 00:50:55,110
and also a skill.

597
00:50:55,740 --> 00:51:00,440
On this matter, I am not on Jung Kyung's side.

598
00:51:01,720 --> 00:51:04,150
I'm on your side.

599
00:51:08,920 --> 00:51:11,380
Joon Young will probably be happy about it too.

600
00:51:13,280 --> 00:51:17,280
After living all these years, I realized that be it for a friends or a siblings relationship,

601
00:51:17,280 --> 00:51:21,110
it has to be balanced for each person to feel at ease.

602
00:51:21,110 --> 00:51:24,400
If only one person is really successful or lags behind,

603
00:51:24,400 --> 00:51:28,450
then some ugly emotions can arise.

604
00:51:29,720 --> 00:51:32,620
 It could all look the same as a student. 

605
00:51:32,620 --> 00:51:34,480
 But once you enter the professional world, 

606
00:51:34,480 --> 00:51:36,580
Some may be the director of a foundation.

607
00:51:36,580 --> 00:51:40,400
Others may be a world-renown musician.

608
00:51:40,400 --> 00:51:41,780
Then someone...

609
00:51:41,780 --> 00:51:46,310
must become a Seoryeong Professor to maintain balance.

610
00:52:00,460 --> 00:52:03,170
Professor Lee Soo Kyung?

611
00:52:03,170 --> 00:52:04,150
Oh, hello.

612
00:52:04,150 --> 00:52:06,830
- You're here? 
 - Wow...

613
00:52:06,830 --> 00:52:11,170
There are so many students of Kyunghoo and you're chasing after each one?

614
00:52:11,170 --> 00:52:13,670
My job is merely to plant the seeds.

615
00:52:13,670 --> 00:52:17,520
We have to watch and make sure those seeds grow.

616
00:52:17,520 --> 00:52:19,690
But do they actually recognize your work?

617
00:52:20,480 --> 00:52:24,910
Oh right, among your 4th-year students should be Chae Song Ah and Kim Hae Na...

618
00:52:24,910 --> 00:52:27,150
Yes? What about them?

619
00:52:27,150 --> 00:52:28,920
Are they also scholarship recipients?

620
00:52:28,920 --> 00:52:30,640
No, they're not.

621
00:52:30,640 --> 00:52:31,970
 Right? 

622
00:52:31,970 --> 00:52:36,120
Hae Na's grades are middling and Song Ah is in last place...

623
00:52:37,270 --> 00:52:41,580
Those two are currently interns in our performance planning team.

624
00:52:41,580 --> 00:52:43,650
Oh really?

625
00:52:43,650 --> 00:52:45,950
I didn't know... Ah.

626
00:52:47,180 --> 00:52:51,930
Hae Na's father is the dean of our school.

627
00:52:51,930 --> 00:52:52,620
Oh, I see...

628
00:52:52,620 --> 00:52:56,050
 She takes after her father so she's smart and well rounded. 

629
00:52:56,050 --> 00:52:58,390
Yes. So is Chae Song Ah.

630
00:52:58,390 --> 00:53:03,580
Song Ah...that girl graduated from our school of business, right?

631
00:53:03,580 --> 00:53:05,100
Yes.

632
00:53:05,100 --> 00:53:06,510
She has a good head about her.

633
00:53:06,510 --> 00:53:09,770
It's just that her violin performance is lacking.

634
00:53:10,800 --> 00:53:13,320
At any rate, Chae Song Ah is a good worker.

635
00:53:13,320 --> 00:53:16,100
She's quick on her feet and is very sensible.

636
00:53:16,100 --> 00:53:17,740
Oh really?

637
00:53:17,740 --> 00:53:20,920
I'm glad that she's at least good at working.

